commitResults.messageTitle: feature: Introduce TARS Chatbot skeleton with hello & goodbye messages.
feature: Implement Level-1 Echo functionality for TARS Chatbot
fix: Echo functionality exits immediately after bye, chatbot reply formatting
feature: Implement Level-2 store functionality for user inputs, display with list command
feature: Implemented Task Class, modified list functionality, mark/unmark command to update task status
refactor: Improve coding standards compliance for TARS chatbot
commitResults.messageBody:
- Added Javadoc comments for all methods to enhance documentation.
- Replaced magic numbers with named constants. Example: maximum task size.
- Renamed variables and methods to follow Java naming conventions.
- Modularized code by extracting program logic into functions.
- Example: mark/unmark logic into 'MarkHandler'
- Improved code formatting and layout for better adherence to style guide.

commitResults.messageTitle: feature: Implemented Level-4 Todo, Event and Deadline functionality - Task class added new Superclass method getSymbol and modified toString - Added new classes Todo, Event and Deadline inherit from Task - new method 'taskParser' that handles user input and creates Task Objects - updated 'addTask' method to handle different class Types. - Improved `printTaskList` formatting for better readability. - Refactored task marking logic into `markHandler` to improve maintainability. - Ensured basic input validation for command parsing.

test: Implemented A-TextUiTesting for automated testing - input.txt updated with commands corresponding to week 4 examples - EXPTECTED.txt updated with expected output - minor changes to TARS to remove trailing whitespaces

refactor: Improve A-CodeQuality for TARS Chatbot. - moved welcome/goodbye messages from multi-line prints to String constants - replaced all instances of leading whitespace in prints to \t characters - updated EXPECTED.txt to accommodate output changes - reduced nesting in taskParser by splitting out switch statement - Utilised abstract declaration for Task to prevent instantiation.

refactor: Started on Level-5 error validation - updated parseCommandType to be case-insensitive, throw exception for empty commands - introduced CommandType Enum to validate string, eliminating magic strings. - minor refactoring to other methods to restructure validation logic

refactor: implemented custom A-Exceptions - introduced new TARSInvalidCommandBodyException to validate command body - created new parseCommandBody function to validate command body based on command type. LIST, MARK, UNMARK validation implemented - updated parseCommandType to throw Exceptions - Try-Catch block in main program loop that handles exceptions from two aforementioned parsing methods - todo: finish validation for all command types. Implement command handler method to be called after validation.

refactor: Implemented Level-5 error validation - Implemented parseCommandBody to validate command arguments and enforce proper structure. - Added validation for /by, /from, /to flags in DEADLINE and EVENT commands. - Ensured MARK and UNMARK commands validate task index before processing. - Refactored commandHandler() to improve separation of responsibility.

refactor: Refined Level-5 Error Validation - Updated TARSInvalidCommandBodyException constructor method to accept error message - Implemented Stretch Goal: error-specific error messages for each Exception - Small changes to validation logic, reordering of validation. - input.txt updated with invalid command test cases - EXPTECTED.txt updated with expected output for invalid cases
Merge Level-5 features

refactor: Restructured TARS into A-Packages - Moved CommandType and TARSInvalidCommandBodException into TARS.command package - Organized Task, Todo, Deadline and Event Classes into TARS.task package - Moved TARS main class into TARS.ui package - Updated all references to reflect new package structure - Modified EXPECTED.txt and runtest.bat to align with updated structure
Merge A-Packages restructuring

refactor: Implemented taskList with A-Collections - taskList implemented with ArrayList instead of Array - updated array indexing with ArrayList Methods e.g. get, add - nTasks can be dynamically represented with taskList.size() - removed nTasks counter variable, updated logic in listing and validation

feature: Implemented Level-6 delete function - implemented new CommandType DELETE to Enum - delete command implemented with same syntax/validation as mark/unmark - created deleteHandler function that handles deletion logic - Added DELETE case to commandHandler - bug-fix to validation: amended search term for hasBy, hasFrom, hasTo flag detection booleans

feature: Implemented Level-7 file storage function - Added writeFile() method to save task list data to /data/data.txt file - Implemented loadFile() method to read task list data from storage. - checkDataPathExists() method ensures data directory/file exits before IO operations - initializeTaskList() method converts stored data into Task objects saved in taskList array - Refactored getTask() method to use by/to/from delimiters to parse String representation of Tasks stored in data file.
merged Level-7 branch
resolved conflict when merging Level-6 branch

refactor: Started on A-MoreOOP increment - Separated functionality into command, logic, task and util packages - new UI class to handle user interactions (e.g. console print, user input) - new Storage class to handle file IO operations (only Load method implemented) - new TaskList class to handle program memory (only initialise method implemented) - new Parser class to parse file/command lines with regex and return Task/Command (only parse File implemented) - new TaskType Enum to represent/validate Todo, Deadline, Event classes - modifications to Task class and subclasses with default constructor, new TaskType attribute - Todo: abstract Command and subclasses, parsing/validation/exception handling for command lines.

refactor: Completed A-MoreOOP increment - new Validator class validates user input before parsing. Throws TARSValidateCommandType/Param exceptions. - Validator class validates 1. CommandType is valid 2. parameters of specific CommandType are valid. - Parser parses input after validation, assumes valid input. Instantiates Command classes to be executed - new Command Abstract class with execute method, which is inherited by specific Command subclasses e.g. AddCommand. - TaskList CRUD methods and toString overwrite that returns all tasks as a contiguous String. - Storage class write method implemented to write data to file. - Updated text-ui-test script and expected outputs to reflect changes in project structure, UI.
refactor: Improved Structure of Parser, Validator - new RegexConstants class to store regex strings used by Parser and Validator - renamed constant regex strings to follow SE-EDU convention

feature: Implemented Level-8 DateTime replacement - DateTimeParser class that handles parsing of DateTime objects from parameter string - Replaces date strings in "yyyy-MM-dd" format to "d MMM yyyy" format (e.g. 2025-03-10 to 10 Mar 2025) - Replaces time strings in "HHmm" format to "h.mm a" format (e.g 0127 to 1.27 am) - Updated ParseTask to implement dateTime replacement when getting new command string

feature: Implemented Level-9 find function - updated CommandType with FIND command - new FindCommand class that implements find functionality - new /find searchterm command that matches the search term to any part of the Task string - Updaded Parser/Validator classes to account for /find functionality
refactor: A-JavaDoc added comments - Added Javadoc comments to multiple classes and methods - Documenting all non-private classes and methods, ensuring clarity and maintainability.
